Private Sub Report_Open(Cancel As Integer)
' These prevent user from changing filter.
Me.FilterOn = True
Me.Filter = "[Status] = 'A' AND (NOT isnull(Win_EXN)) and Win_EXN <> 98 " & _
             "and Win_Exn <> 99 and Win_Exn <> 95 and Win_Exn <> 0 and Type <> 'S'"
' rev 540
  Dim MyFilter As String
  MyFilter = InputBox("This report takes a while to prepare - be patient" & vbCrLf & _
           vbCrLf & "Select An Option: " & vbCrLf & _
           " A  ALL Winners (normal)" & vbCrLf & _
           " S  Senior Winners" & vbCrLf & _
           " J  Junior Winners" & vbCrLf & _
           " E  A Winning Exhibit Number.")
  MyFilter = UCase(MyFilter)
  If MyFilter = "A" Then Exit Sub
  If MyFilter = "E" Then
     MyFilter = InputBox("Enter Exhibit Number", "Exhibit Number")
     Me.Filter = Me.Filter & " and EXN = " & MyFilter
     Exit Sub
  End If
  If MyFilter = "S" Or MyFilter = "J" Then
     Me.Filter = Me.Filter & " and ExDIV = '" & MyFilter & "'"
  End If


End Sub
